subject: Golf
lead_paragraph: Momoko Ueda became the first Japanese winner of the Mizuno Classic in nine years, closing with a five-under 66 that included a double eagle. Ueda held off Reilley Rankin and Maria Hjorth to win by two strokes. She finished at 13-under 203 in Shima, Japan, and earned $210,000 for her first L.P.G.A. Tour victory.
